                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12738128" author="tmoore" created="Sun, 2 Aug 2009 20:54:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a simple work around: in a project&apos;s properties section, explicitly redefine these properties:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;project.organization.name&amp;gt;${project.organization.name}&amp;lt;/project.organization.name&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;project.organization.url&amp;gt;${project.organization.url}&amp;lt;/project.organization.url&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12738205" author="tmoore" created="Mon, 3 Aug 2009 06:47:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch with a unit test and a fix. I&apos;m not sure if this is the optimal way to fix the problem, but it works for my case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12750709" author="mcculls" created="Wed, 2 Sep 2009 22:48:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied modified version of the patch in trunk (r810723)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757372" author="tmoore" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2009 19:25:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed: 2.0.1 fixes my problem. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
